<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10641:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                    Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-05T11:00:00-04:00">May 5, 1941—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>77. Referring to the Department’s circular telegram of April 29, 10 p.m.,
                            Bolivian Minister for Foreign Affairs<note n="10" xml:id="d47fn1">Eduardo Anze Matienzo.</note> tells me he has already indicated
                            informally to Spanish authorities advisability of refraining from
                            actively supporting Axis Powers and he does not feel it would be helpful
                            for him to take further action individually in this matter.</p>
                        <p>However he suggests that joint action would be more helpful and he is
                            prepared to consider such a plan if other Latin American countries are
                            of similar view.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>